{
  "text": "Such environmental-induced effects have also been observed for the G and 2D Raman signals of graphene [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and the Raman modes of TMDs [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] , as summarized in Figures S5 and S6 (see Supplementary Information). Again, the MST accurately accounts for the Raman intensities of the G and 2D modes of SL graphene ( Figure  S5a ) and the A 1g and E mode measured in MoS 2 nanoflakes of different thicknesses supported on SiO 2 /Si substrates, as extracted from Ref. [CITATION_7] . The good match observed between experimental results and the trend obtained by means of the MST indicates that the model also accurately accounts for the variation of the Raman intensity signals due to changes in the thickness of the active material.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "118633771",
    "[CITATION_2]": "14820510",
